/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Here is another snippet for consideration -- copied from [this example](https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/webgl_simple_gi.html):\r\n```javascript\r\n\/\/ HACK:\r\n\r\nTHREE.Mesh.prototype.clone = function () {\r\n\r\n\tvar newMaterial = ( this.material.isMaterial ) ? this.material.clone() : this.material.slice();\r\n\r\n\treturn new this.constructor( this.geometry.clone(), newMaterial ).copy( this );\r\n\r\n};\r\n```","created_at":"2018-10-30T03:54:55.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15064#issuecomment-434163080","id":434163080,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15064","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzNDE2MzA4MA==","updated_at":"2018-10-30T03:54:55.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/434163080","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Cloning geometry and textures can all get expensive; we go to lengths to ensure that GLTFLoader reuses geometry whenever possible. I would \u2014 in particular \u2014 be sad if cloning or copying a material meant cloning its textures.\r\n\r\nTo focus on the `copy()` pattern options first, since `clone()` may hang on that \u2014\u00a0\r\n\r\n1. `this.material.copy( source.material );` \u2014 I don't find this intuitive; it isn't obvious that when cloning an object I should want to keep its material _type_ but overwrite that material's properties.\r\n\r\n2. `this.material = source.material;` \u2014 This seems reasonable. What are the downsides, except that a user may be surprised when modifying the new object's material affects the old object?\r\n\r\n3. `this.material = source.material.clone()` This also seems reasonable, so long as textures are not cloned (and they aren't currently). I assume, but haven't recently checked, that cloned materials still only result in one shader program?\r\n\r\nIt doesn't look like the `copy()` method of `THREE.Mesh` touches geometry or material at all... that is another option for `THREE.Line` et al, yes?","created_at":"2018-10-30T18:38:29.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/15064#issuecomment-434420894","id":434420894,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/15064","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzNDQyMDg5NA==","updated_at":"2018-10-30T18:38:45.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/434420894","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1848368?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.